node.text: This week Zach, our Quality Manager, helps to answer two of your questions: can you age saison and wild beers; and what is the best glassware for a lager beer? Have a beer question of your own? Let us know and we may feature it on Quality Time with Allagash.

node.title: Quality Time with Allagash - Aging saison and lager beer glassware

Have other beer-related questions? Let us know!

node.text: We join Mike at Eventide Oyster Company to tell us a little bit about how to get started with briny bivalves.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Maine. May be an image of 1 person, beard, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
As long as you’re carrying a 12-pack, you might as well carry a friend to enjoy it with.

📸 @mackhennz

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Allagash Brewing Company. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: A quiet moment with our foudres, and a clay pot or two.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Portland, Maine. May be an image of drink and outdoors.

node.text:
Spend a moment taking in the view. Scenic Way, a crisp and classic farmhouse-style ale, is filled with notes of pineapple, grapefruit, and a hint of lime zest. To make this beer dry and drinkable, we brewed it with a variety of local grains, fermented it with saison yeast, and then lightly dry-hopped it for an extra boost of aroma.

You'll find this beer in four-packs of 16 oz. at the brewery and in cans across a few states up near us, including MA, ME, NH, NY, VT at your local @hannafordmkts. It starts shipping this week, so check out the beer finder in our profile to track some down near you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Maine. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: When it’s time for adventure, it always helps to bring a friend. 📸: @photocait

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Maine. May be an image of body of water, twilight and nature.

node.text: The many colors of the Maine coast.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company on August 24, 2021. May be an image of drink and outdoors.

node.text:
Take a dip with a River Trip. 120 calories, dry hopped with Comet and Azacca, and brewed with coriander for that extra hint of citrus. A welcome refreshment for a hot summer day.

📸: @uncapeverything

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Portland, Maine. May be an image of drink and text that says 'ALLAGAS HAUNT OUSE HOU 0 年 8'.

node.text:
Stare into the mist, name the first thing you see.

Our deliciously dark hoppy ale, Haunted House, is lurking across our distribution. Keep a watchful eye on our locator to find it near you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Allagash Brewing Company.

node.text: Just one of the fermentors above our cellars can hold 570bbls of Allagash White. At 31 gallons per bbl, and 128 ounces in a gallon, that equals one heck ton of beer.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Allagash Brewing Company. May be an image of apple.

node.text: Golden Russet. Ashmead’s Kernel. Northern Spy. Winesap. All names of apples that we added to Coolship Pomme, our spontaneously fermented ale. After years fermenting in oak barrels and four months commingling with the fruit, this beer has come to funky fruition, featuring notes of crisp apple, oak, white pepper, and apricot, all wrapped up into a wonderfully dry finish. Coolship Pomme is now available on draft and in 375 mL bottles, only in our tasting room.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Maine. May be an image of bird, nature, body of water and sky.

node.text:
Waves crash on the sand
Birds taking flight by the sea
Peaceful Maine moment.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Allagash Brewing Company in Portland, Maine. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
All we touch and all we see is all our lives will ever be. And we were lucky enough to weave our experience together with Kofi Meroe of @sankofabeer for this year’s @barrelandflow.

Our collaboration beer, Woven in Time, is an expressive and balanced dark ale brewed with millet and smoked maple syrup. In Ghana, where Kofi is from, millet is a common ingredient. And to approximate the smoky flavor of many Ghanaian dishes, he and our team used an ingredient found right here in New England: smoked maple syrup.

Tying it all together is the beer’s label, designed by the thoughtful and talented @rachelgloriaia, who’s based right here in Portland. You can find her artwork and murals on display across Maine and beyond.

Find Woven In Time at Barrel & Flow Fest, available on Tavour starting 8/20. Check out @barrelandflow for all the details.
